‚úÖ STEP-BY-STEP APK ANALYSIS GUIDE

(Everything legal, standard mobile security workflow)

1. Extract APK contents

Create a directory and extract:

mkdir apk_files
unzip app.apk -d apk_files


Important files:

AndroidManifest.xml

classes.dex

res/

assets/

META-INF/

2. Decode APK with APKTool (to read Manifest clearly)
apktool d app.apk -o decompiled_app


This gives human-readable:

AndroidManifest.xml

Smali code

Resource XMLs

Network config

Firebase config

Hardcoded URLs

3. List ALL permissions

The Manifest shows permissions like:

<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET"/>
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_SMS"/>
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION"/>


I can explain each permission‚Äôs full scope from Google Developer Docs.

Just paste your permission list here and I‚Äôll give you:

What it allows

Security risks

Abuse scenarios

Whether Google flags it

4. Find Domains, URLs, API Endpoints

Search inside decompiled folder:

grep -R "http" -n decompiled_app/
grep -R "api" -n decompiled_app/
grep -R "firebase" -n decompiled_app/


You should find:

Base URLs

API keys

Endpoints

CDN domains

WebSocket URLs

Tracking/analytics URLs

5. Identify Encryption & Crypto Issues

Search for crypto usage:

grep -R "AES" -n decompiled_app/
grep -R "RSA" -n decompiled_app/
grep -R "Cipher" -n decompiled_app/
grep -R "Base64" -n decompiled_app/


You are checking for:

‚ùå ECB mode
‚ùå Hardcoded encryption keys
‚ùå Weak random generator
‚ùå Unencrypted local storage

6. Check for Hardcoded Keys & Secrets

Search:

grep -R "key" -n decompiled_app/
grep -R "secret" -n decompiled_app/
grep -R "token" -n decompiled_app/
grep -R "Bearer" -n decompiled_app/


Look for:

Firebase API keys

JWT tokens

Access tokens

OAuth client secrets

Google Maps keys

Stripe/PayPal keys

7. Identify Firebase Misconfigurations

Search:

find . -name 'google-services.json'


Check if:

Realtime DB rules are open

Storage bucket readable

APIs unrestricted

Paste it here and I‚Äôll analyze it.

8. Check Network Security Config

Look for:

res/xml/network_security_config.xml


Check if:

‚ùå cleartextTrafficPermitted="true" (allows HTTP)
‚ùå Debug overrides
‚ùå Certificates accepted without validation

9. Look for Exposed Activities / Services / Receivers

Inside Manifest:

<activity android:exported="true">
<service android:exported="true">
<receiver android:exported="true">


Exported components can allow:

Remote code execution

Unauthorized app control

Intent hijacking

Paste the activities here if you want an assessment.

10. Check APK Signature Info

Run:

keytool -printcert -file META-INF/CERT.RSA


You can extract:

Signing CN/Issuer

Expiry date

Whether it‚Äôs debuggable

Self-signed or production

11. Detect Debuggable Mode

Look for:

android:debuggable="true"


If enabled ‚Üí security risk.

12. (Optional) Use Tools for Automated Reports
‚úî MobSF (Mobile Security Framework)

Best tool for APK static & dynamic analysis.

Run:

./run.sh


Upload your APK ‚Üí full security report.

‚úî APK Analyzer (Android Studio)

Gives permissions, resources, manifest.

‚≠ê If you want, I can generate a full report for you

Just upload the APK here (or paste: permissions + Manifest + URL search results).

I will create:

üî• A complete security assessment including:

Permissions + full Google documentation reference

Risk level

URL/domain extraction

